pdated software (programming tools, design software, etc.), and high-speed internet connectivity. The campus is Wi-Fi enabled , allowing students and staff to access learning materials anywhere. IT support teams ensure system maintenance, cybersecurity, and uninterrupted services. 3. Administrative Office This is the central hub for all administrative activities. It manages student admissions, fee collection, scholarships, examination records, certificates, and official communication. The office includes sections like accounts, examination cell, and registrar office. It ensures smooth coordination between students, faculty, and management. Administrative Office is equipped with Cloud based ERP Software. 4. Smart Classrooms Classrooms are equipped with projectors, interactive boards, audio systems, and multimedia tools. These facilities enable teachers to deliver engaging lectures using presentations, videos, and digital content, making learning more interactive and effective. 5. Medical Facility The campus health center provides basic medical care and first aid services to students and staff. Tie-ups with nearby hospitals ensure quick medical assistance when needed. 6. Sports & Gym Facilities Sports facilities promote physical fitness and overall well-being. College have playground for outdoor games like cricket, football, and athletics. A well-equipped gymnasium with fitness trainers helps students maintain a healthy lifestyle. 7. Canteen The canteen provides affordable, hygienic, and nutritious food to students and staff. It serves meals, snacks, beverages, and sometimes regional cuisines. It also acts as a social space where students relax, interact, and spend leisure time between classes. 8. Hostel Facility Hostels provide safe and comfortable accommodation for outstation students. Facilities include furnished rooms, clean drinking water, mess services, study areas. Security, wardens, and strict rules ensure discipline and safety. Separate hostels are available for boys and girls. 9. Internet & Wi-Fi College equipped with high-speed internet access across the campus. Students can use it for research, online classes, assignments, and communication. Secure login systems and firewalls maintain safe usage and protect against cyber threats. 10. Security & Surveillance Campus safety is ensured through 24/7 security personnel, CCTV surveillance. Security systems monitor activities and help maintain discipline, prevent unauthorized access, and respond quickly to emergencies. 11. Seminar Hall The Seminar Hall is use for cultural events, seminars, workshops, conferences, and guest lectures. It is equipped with modern audio-visual systems and seating arrangements to host 300 audiences. 12. Training and Placement Cell This cell supports students in building their careers by organizing training programs, resume workshops, mock interviews, and internships. It connects students with companies for campus recruitment and helps them prepare for job opportunities and higher education. Important Links: About RES About College Central Facility College Development Committee Institutional Development Plan College Advisery Board Local Management Committee Chairman's Message Vice Chairman's Message Principal's Message Syllabus Open Syllabus of All Courses! REV. CBCS UG COURSES (Revised CBCS) UG FY 2019-20 B.Sc (CS) - FY B.Sc (SE) - FY B.Sc (NT) - FY B.Sc (BT) - FY BCA - FY UG SY 2020-21 BCA SY B.Sc (CS) - SY B.Sc (SE) - SY B.Sc (NT) - SY UG TY 2021-22 BCA TY B.Sc. (CS) - TY B.Sc. (SE) - TY B.Sc. (NT) - TY B.Voc(SD) - FY SY TY BBA - TY B.Sc.Biotechnology - TY UG TY 2025-26 BCA TY B.Sc. (CS) - TY B.Sc. (SE) - TY B.Sc. (NT) - TY B.Sc. (CM) - TY B.Sc. (IT) - TY Note: Updated Revised CBCS Syllabus (TY) Uploaded on 13.09.2025 --> TY 2023-24 B.Sc.IT - FY SY TY B.Sc.CM - FY SY TY PG COURSES (Revised CBCS) PG FY Syllabus 2019-20 M.Sc (CS) - FY M.Sc (SE) - FY M.Sc (CM) - FY M.Sc (SAN)- FY M.Sc (BT) - FY PG SY Syllabus 2020-21 M.Sc (CS)- SY M.Sc (SE)- SY M.S